Subject: [PATCH] backend/libinput: add default case to switch-type switch

Current Arch / recent toolchains build wlroots with `-Werror=switch` (or
effectively that via distro CFLAGS), and libinput's `enum libinput_switch`
is not exhaustively covered by the switch statement in
`handle_switch_toggle` — only `LIBINPUT_SWITCH_LID` and
`LIBINPUT_SWITCH_TABLET_MODE` are handled.

If a newer libinput introduces an additional enum value, or the compiler
is strict about this, the build fails at
`subprojects/wlroots/libwlroots-0.18.a.p/backend_libinput_switch.c.o`.

Add a trivial `default: return;` so unknown switch types are silently
ignored instead of producing a compile error. This matches the
behaviour we already want — we genuinely cannot synthesise a
`wlr_switch_toggle_event` for a switch type wlroots has no mapping for.

Applies cleanly to Valve's wlroots-gamescope branch at 0.18-gamescope5.

---
diff --git a/backend/libinput/switch.c b/backend/libinput/switch.c
index abeec86d..51fb5da8 100644
--- a/backend/libinput/switch.c
+++ b/backend/libinput/switch.c
@@ -36,6 +36,8 @@ void handle_switch_toggle(struct libinput_event *event,
 	case LIBINPUT_SWITCH_TABLET_MODE:
 		wlr_event.switch_type = WLR_SWITCH_TYPE_TABLET_MODE;
 		break;
+	default:
+		return;
 	}
 	switch (libinput_event_switch_get_switch_state(sevent)) {
 	case LIBINPUT_SWITCH_STATE_OFF:
